      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOMB ROCKY (2) chased the lead early from the inside and boxed on well to finish second, beaten 9 lengths (30.65) at Sandown in a T3 Grade 5 H over 515m. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and six minor placings to her credit. Makes plenty of appeal. COMPTON TIG (5) finds it hard to win but looks close to breaking through. Finished in the minors last time when third (23.57) at this track making it back to back placings. Overdue and is among the main hopes. STARLIGHT JEWEL (1) was sent out long odds last time but charged out of the boxes with a fast early sectional and gave a sight before being swallowed up late, finishing a 2 length fourth (23.17) over 400m at this track. Worth another chance. MAGIC POPPY (7) was out of the money at this circuit last start but can make amends.",
